{
  "stem": "19198.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Elementary school was a-- a very important part of-- of everyday life and the-- as you probably know, in Germany the teacher, the herr [GERMAN] the fraulein [GERMAN], was a [GERMAN], a person whom both you as a person and the public respected.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I do remember several of the teachers, not all, and they had the problem of-- of dealing with a-- a young student who by age four was able to read fluently and then comes into a first grade where they have to teach the-- the letters of the alphabet.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So but I always had a good relationship with my teachers, even with teachers whom the rest of the students considered difficult and-- and very strict.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Especially I remember my fourth grade teacher, who took a special interest in me, Herr [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they frequently would give me extra assignments because I was able to work a little faster than others.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what was, I believe, much more important to the-- in the German schools than in American schools, they-- the ranks of the top students were always known and usually, I was the number one student, the primos, as they called the top student.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But sometimes a-- a girl that lived in right in my neighborhood would grab that place away from me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were very friendly competitors and usually walked to school together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That would have been in 1921 or-- yeah, 1921.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 17 and a half.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had almost only non-Jewish friends because I was the only Jewish child of my age in the town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- for a while, two brothers from a nearby town who attended school in-- in Eberbach would stay in town over Shabbat because they would not ride the train, which they did on the other days.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
